Given locally strategyproof single-item auctions, the sequential auction problem exists for a bidder if and only if either of the following two conditions is true: (1) within the set of interesting bundles (a) there are two  bundles that are substitutes, (b) there is an item with uncertain marginal value, or (c) there is an item that is over-supplied; (2) a bidder faces competitors" bids that are conditioned on the bidder"s past bids.
